#. Tag: title
#: art_amd-sev.xml:349
#, no-c-format
msgid "VM installation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_amd-sev.xml:350
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>virt-install</command> supports the installation of SEV and SEV-ES "
"virtual machines. In addition to your standard installation parameters, "
"provide <command>virt-install</command> with options to satisfy the VM "
"requirements and the <literal>--launchSecurity</literal> option."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_amd-sev.xml:356
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following example starts a network installation of a SLES15 SP4 virtual "
"machine protected with SEV-ES."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_amd-sev.xml:360
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"   virt-install --name sles15sp4-sev-es --location http://192.168.0.1/"
"install/sles15sp4/x86_64 --disk size=20 --network=bridge=br0,model=virtio,"
"rom.bar=off <co xml:id=\"sec-amd-sev-ex-rombar\"/> --vcpus 4 --memory 4096 --"
"noautoconsole --events on_reboot=destroy --machine q35 --memtune "
"hard_limit=4563402 --launchSecurity sev,policy=0x07 <co xml:id=\"sec-amd-sev-"
"ex-launchsec\"/> --boot firmware=efi <co xml:id=\"sec-amd-sev-ex-fw\"/> --"
"vnc --serial pty\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_amd-sev.xml:365
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The iPXE option ROM is not compatible with SEV-encrypted VMs and must be "
"disabled on all virtio-net devices. While libvirt supports disabling option "
"ROMs using either the <literal>enabled</literal> or <literal>bar</literal> "
"attributes of the the <tag class=\"element\">rom</tag> element, virt-install "
"only supports disabling option ROMs using the <literal>bar</literal> "
"attribute."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_amd-sev.xml:374
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <literal>launchSecurity</literal> option specifies the type and policy "
"to be enforced by the SEV firmware. The policy setting is described in <xref "
"linkend=\"table-guestpolicy\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_amd-sev.xml:381
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <literal>boot</literal> option allows specifying many boot-related "
"settings, including the firmware used by the virtual machine. Specifying a "
"firmware type <literal>efi</literal> allows libvirt's firmware auto-"
"selection feature to select an appropriate SEV capable firmware for the "
"virtual machine."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_amd-sev.xml:392
#, no-c-format
msgid "SEV with &kubevirt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_amd-sev.xml:393
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kubevirt; supports running SEV guests starting from the version "
"<literal>0.49.0</literal> . The functionality can be activated by enabling "
"the <literal>WorkloadEncryptionSEV</literal> feature gate:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_amd-sev.xml:398
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"&prompt.user;kubectl edit kubevirt kubevirt -n kubevirt\n"
"[...]\n"
"spec:\n"
"  configuration:\n"
"    developerConfiguration:\n"
"      featureGates:\n"
"      - WorkloadEncryptionSEV\n"
"[...]\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_amd-sev.xml:408
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To run an SEV-encrypted guest, the virtual machine specification must "
"include the entry <literal>sev: {}</literal> under the "
"<literal>launchSecurity</literal> domain element. Additionally, you need to "
"configure the <literal>firmware/bootloader</literal> parameters to use the "
"<literal>efi</literal> option with the <literal>secureBoot</literal> flag "
"set to <literal>disabled</literal> . The corresponding YAML snippet will "
"look similar to the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_amd-sev.xml:415
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"[...]\n"
"spec:\n"
"  domain:\n"
"    firmware:\n"
"      bootloader:\n"
"        efi:\n"
"          secureBoot: false\n"
"    launchSecurity:\n"
"      sev: {}\n"
"[...]\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_amd-sev.xml:430
#, no-c-format
msgid "Current limitations"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_amd-sev.xml:431
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"SUSE does not recommend using the SEV and SEV-ES features with SUSE Linux "
"products on the first generation AMD EPYC™ 7000 series of processors, "
"codename Naples. It is recommended to use at least the second generation "
"7002 series processors, codename Rome. Additionally, the following "
"limitations are placed on SEV and SEV-ES VMs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_amd-sev.xml:440
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The guest operating system running inside an SEV-encrypted VM must contain "
"SEV support. &sls; 12 SP4 and newer, and all &sls; 15 releases support SEV."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_amd-sev.xml:446
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Any operations that involve saving and restoring the memory and state of an "
"instance are currently not supported. This means that SEV-encrypted VMs "
"cannot be resumed from snapshots, saved/restored, or live migrated. "
"Encrypted VMs can be shutdown and restarted on another host as normal."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_amd-sev.xml:454
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"SEV-encrypted VMs cannot contain directly-accessible host devices (that is, "
"PCI passthrough)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_amd-sev.xml:460
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"SEV-encrypted VMs are not compatible with Secure Boot. UEFI firmwares "
"containing Secure Boot support will not work with SEV or SEV-ES VMs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_amd-sev.xml:466
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"SEV-ES VMs cannot be rebooted from within using <command>reboot</command> , "
"<command>shutdown -r now</command> , etc. A reboot must be done by shutting "
"down the VM and starting it again. This limitation does not apply to SEV "
"VMs, only SEV-ES."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_amd-sev.xml:474
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These limitations will be removed in the future as the hardware, firmware, "
"and various layers of software receive new features."
msgstr ""

